articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Several Egyptian border guards sustained minor injuries on Sunday after being accidentally hit by fragments of a shell from an Israeli tank, a spokesperson for the Egyptian army said.
articles.title: Egyptian army says border guards hurt in accidental hit by Israeli tank

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israel's military has warned Gaza residents that they risk being identified as accomplices "in a terrorist organisation" if they do not move south, Palestinians there said, amid growing humanitarian fears with little aid being allowed in.
articles.title: New Israeli warning to Gaza residents as first aid trickles in

articles.author: Kanishka Singh
articles.description: The U.S. State Department said on Sunday U.S. citizens should not travel to Iraq after recent attacks on American troops and personnel in the region.
articles.title: US advises citizens not to travel to Iraq after recent attacks on US personnel

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A second convoy of aid trucks entered the Egyptian side of the Rafah border crossing on Sunday, heading towards the Gaza Strip, according to Egyptian security and humanitarian sources at Rafah.
articles.title: Second aid convoy enters Egyptian side of Rafah crossing en route to Gaza, sources say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israeli aircraft struck a compound beneath a mosque in the occupied West Bank early on Sunday that the military said was being used by militants to organise attacks, and Palestinian medics said at least one person was killed.
articles.title: Israel strikes militant compound under West Bank mosque, military says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thousands of people waving Palestinian flags and chanting "Gaza, Paris is with you" gathered on Sunday for the first pro-Palestinian demonstration allowed by police in the French capital since the Oct. 7 Hamas attacks on Israel.
articles.title: Thousands join Paris's first authorised pro-Palestinian demo since Hamas attacks

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Church of England's spiritual head said on Sunday he had "no idea" how many people died in a blast last week at an Anglican hospital in the Gaza Strip, and that assuming Israeli culpability could be tantamount to antisemitic libel.
articles.title: Archbishop of Canterbury warns against assuming Israel behind Gaza hospital blast

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Emily Rose
articles.description: Israel pounded southern Gaza with air strikes early on Sunday and said it would intensify its attacks in the enclave's north, as the U.S. committed to getting more aid to Palestinians running out of food, water, medicines and fuel.
articles.title: Israel to intensify Gaza strikes, U.S. pushes for more aid

articles.author: Parisa Hafezi, Jonathan Saul, Arshad Mohammed
articles.description: On Oct. 15, Iran issued a stinging public ultimatum to its arch-enemy Israel: Halt your onslaught on Gaza or we'll be forced to take action, its foreign minister warned.
articles.title: Iran's quandary: How to stay out of Israel's war on Hamas

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China and the Philippines traded accusations over a collision in disputed waters of the South China Sea as Chinese vessels blocked Philippine boats supplying forces there on Sunday, the latest in a series of maritime confrontations.
articles.title: China, Philippines trade accusations over South China Sea collision
